post_cb({"4325844": {"ParentId": "4325802", "CommentCount": "4", "Body": "<p>No. In C I get this error:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_4325802_4325844_0\">test.c:2: error: non-static declaration of \u2018i\u2019 follows static declaration<br>\n  test.c:1: note: previous definition of \u2018i\u2019 was here </br></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In C++, these:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_4325802_4325844_1\">test.cpp:2: error: redefinition of \u2018int i\u2019<br>\n  test.cpp:1: error: \u2018int i\u2019 previously defined here</br></p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "338803", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "4325844", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2010-12-01T15:19:37.113", "LastActivityDate": "2010-12-01T15:19:37.113"}, "4325802": {"CommentCount": "4", "AcceptedAnswerId": "4325865", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "338803", "CreationDate": "2010-12-01T15:16:21.447", "LastActivityDate": "2010-12-01T15:46:20.793", "LastEditDate": "2010-12-01T15:17:17.380", "ViewCount": "207", "FavoriteCount": "0", "Title": "Changing the linkage of a name", "Id": "4325802", "Score": "7", "Body": "<p>An attempt to change the linkage of a name <code>i</code> is made in this code. Is it legal in C/C++?</p>\n<pre><code>static int i = 2;\nint i;\n\nint main()\n{\n   return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c>", "OwnerUserId": "507271", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "4325865": {"ParentId": "4325802", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>In C++ your code is ill-formed (you have multiple <em>definitions</em> of variable <code>i</code>) i.e a standard conformant compiler is required to issue an error message</p>\n<p>$3.2.1 (C++03)</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_4325802_4325865_0\">No translation unit shall contain more than one definition of any variable, function, class type, enumeration type or template. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In C99 your code invokes Undefined Behaviour because 6.2.2/7 says</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_4325802_4325865_1\">If,  within  a  translation  unit,  the  same  identi\ufb01er  appears  with  both  internal  and  external linkage, the behavior is <strong>unde\ufb01ned</strong>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "165520", "LastEditorUserId": "165520", "LastEditDate": "2010-12-01T15:46:20.793", "Id": "4325865", "Score": "10", "CreationDate": "2010-12-01T15:21:34.143", "LastActivityDate": "2010-12-01T15:46:20.793"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_4325802_4325865_0": {"section_id": 7038, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}}, "n3337": {"so_4325802_4325865_0": {"section_id": 6784, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}}, "n4659": {"so_4325802_4325865_0": {"section_id": 8535, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}, "so_4325802_4325865_1": {"section_id": 8640, "quality": 0.6666666666666666, "length": 8}}}});